# Active Directory Home Lab

## Project Overview
This project demonstrates the deployment and administration of Microsoft Active Directory in a Windows Server environment. The lab was built to practice common System Administrator and Help Desk tasks.

## Skills Demonstrated
- Active Directory Domain Services (AD DS)
- Creating Organizational Units (OUs)
- Creating and managing users
- Creating security groups
- Password resets
- Account lockout management
- Group Policy basics
- User account administration

## Lab Environment
- Windows Server 2022
- Windows 10 Client
- VMware Workstation
- Active Directory Users and Computers (ADUC)

## Project Tasks
- Installed Active Directory Domain Services
- Promoted the server to a Domain Controller
- Created Organizational Units
- Added users
- Added security groups
- Reset user passwords
- Tested user logins

